WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.467
<i>Previously, on "Stitchers"...</i>

00:01.492 --> 00:04.728
His father is James Miller, the man
behind the $3 billion Ponzi scheme

00:04.753 --> 00:06.923
that wiped out how many
people's life savings?

00:06.948 --> 00:08.717
He died. The funeral was yesterday.

00:08.742 --> 00:10.621
Kirsten, meet my brother.

00:10.646 --> 00:12.089
You can take the girl
out of the trailer,

00:12.114 --> 00:14.815
- but you can't take the trash...
- What the hell is wrong with you?

00:14.840 --> 00:15.898
Amanda, go!

00:17.879 --> 00:20.946
- Thanks for saving my life.
- I was just so afraid of losing you.

00:20.971 --> 00:22.850
My life makes
sense with you in it.

00:22.875 --> 00:24.518
- Are you still working with Stinger?
- No.

00:24.544 --> 00:26.243
I am not working with my father.

00:26.268 --> 00:29.488
I know where my mother is. I didn't
feel right about keeping that from you.

00:29.513 --> 00:31.583
Inside that cabinet,
there's a device

00:31.608 --> 00:33.641
that's connected to how
our cases get picked.

00:33.676 --> 00:35.442
Remember how I said I'd
help you save your mother?

00:35.466 --> 00:36.414
I meant it.

00:36.440 --> 00:39.069
We both have criminal,
absent, pathetic fathers.

00:39.094 --> 00:41.060
Except the only difference is
you're desperate to find yours

00:41.085 --> 00:42.960
and all I want to do is forget mine.

00:45.065 --> 00:46.767
Cameron?

00:50.806 --> 00:52.439
Guess what I have?

00:52.570 --> 00:53.972
What?

00:53.997 --> 00:56.418
Early Spielberg.

00:56.443 --> 00:59.344
"Duel," "The Sugarland Express,"

00:59.369 --> 01:01.687
and please don't tell your mother,

01:01.978 --> 01:03.189
"Jaws."

01:03.608 --> 01:04.974
Thanks.

01:04.998 --> 01:06.871
Hey. Why the face?

01:06.896 --> 01:10.529
Richie Freedman wanted to
come over. Mom said no.

01:10.646 --> 01:12.562
Again. Germs.

01:12.762 --> 01:15.845
Can he please come over, Dad?

01:17.966 --> 01:20.020
You had heart surgery, Cam.

01:20.767 --> 01:23.001
Richie's a great guy, he's a lot of fun,

01:23.026 --> 01:24.893
but when the two of you get going...

01:24.928 --> 01:26.675
You still gotta take it easy.

01:26.700 --> 01:30.090
For how long? It's been over a year!

01:30.465 --> 01:33.822
Everything is gonna be
great one day, Cam.

01:33.847 --> 01:35.747
I promise you.

01:41.798 --> 01:45.824
Excuse me, Sir. Any word on James
Miller? It's been two hours.

01:45.849 --> 01:47.367
He's been told you're here.

01:47.392 --> 01:50.936
Attention.
Code 1. I have code 1A, Area 5.

01:50.961 --> 01:53.002
- Sorry, Sir. You need to leave.
- What's going on?

01:53.027 --> 01:54.273
Fire alarm.

01:54.298 --> 01:55.940
Ma'am. Ma'am.

01:55.965 --> 01:59.603
All visitors proceed
to the nearest exit.

01:59.628 --> 02:00.988
It's just weird, you know?

02:01.013 --> 02:03.207
Yeah, I didn't even know
you wanted to see him.

02:03.232 --> 02:06.227
It's been, what... 13 years?

02:06.252 --> 02:08.252
- Fourteen.
- Hm.

02:08.300 --> 02:10.393
- So, why now?
- I don't know.

02:10.418 --> 02:12.151
I guess Linus's father dying

02:12.176 --> 02:13.627
affected me more than I realized.

02:13.652 --> 02:16.386
Or feelings for you are making me
want to reach out to my family.

02:16.411 --> 02:17.464
That's sweet.

02:17.489 --> 02:19.514
Well, not so sweet that
he wanted to see me.

02:21.148 --> 02:22.941
Well, look. It's a prison.

02:22.966 --> 02:25.390
The delay could have been anything.

02:25.573 --> 02:26.839
I don't know.

02:26.864 --> 02:28.776
Maybe it was just a stupid
idea to go in the first place.

02:32.747 --> 02:35.168
Hey, what's up? Welcome back.

02:35.193 --> 02:36.420
I need everyone back here.

02:36.445 --> 02:37.771
Okay, but why don't you text like usual?

02:37.796 --> 02:40.863
- Why the call?
- Something has happened to your father.

02:40.888 --> 02:42.955
He's under lockdown.

02:45.603 --> 02:48.935
We have a new case that
requires us to break protocol.

02:48.960 --> 02:51.428
Oh good, we haven't pissed
off the NSA in hours.

02:51.453 --> 02:52.950
- Not now, Camille.
- What's up?

02:52.975 --> 02:56.104
- Fisher?
- Victim is Gary Parsons, 55.

02:56.129 --> 02:58.963
A veteran officer with the
Federal Bureau of Prisons.

02:58.999 --> 03:01.465
Had a clean record and a
history of commendations

03:01.490 --> 03:03.456
until he was killed earlier today.

03:03.481 --> 03:05.644
By James Miller.

03:07.000 --> 03:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:23.264 --> 03:26.663
